enberg, Freudenstadt, Württemberg, Germany","nameMeanings":[{"name":"von","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Altered form of Welsh   Vaughan  .","Chinese: variant of   Wong  .","Cambodian: written វ៉ុន, unexplained."],"variants":[{"name":"Vaughan","meanings":["Welsh: from <i>fychan</i>, a lenited form of <i>bychan</i>, a diminutive of <i>bach</i> ‘little’. This was often used to distinguish the younger of two bearers of the same personal name, typically the son of a father with the same name."]}]},{"name":"Diessen","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Reinhard, Erwin.","German: possibly a habitational name from Riessen in Brandenburg.","German: variant of   Riesen  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Riesen","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Armin, Kurt.","German and Swiss German:","habitational name from any of several places so named in Bavaria, Württemberg, and Tyrol."]}]},{"name":"Gisela","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["from <i>gisil</i> ‘pledge’ or ‘scion’.  See  <b>Giselle</b> ."],"variants":[{"name":"Giselle","meanings":["name of Frankish origin, from the Germanic word <i>gisil</i> ‘pledge’. It was a common practice in medieval Europe to leave children as pledges for an alliance, to be brought up at a foreign court, and the name may be derived as a byname from this practice. This was the name by which the wife of  Duke Rollo  of Normandy (  <i>c.</i>860– <i>c.</i>930 ) was known. On her account the name enjoyed considerable popularity in France from an early period. Use of the name in English-speaking countries is much more recent, and is due mainly to the ballet Giselle (first performed in  1841 )."]}]},{"name":"von","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Short form of   Ronald .  It is sometimes used as a given name in its own right."],"variants":[{"name":"Ronald","meanings":["From the Old Norse personal name <i>Rögnvaldr</i> (composed of <i>regin</i> ‘advice, decision’ (also, ‘the gods’) + <i>valdr</i> ‘ruler’). This name was regularly used in the Middle Ages in northern England and Scotland, where Scandinavian influence was strong. It is now widespread throughout the English-speaking world."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Gisela von Andechs von Diessen was born about 1125, in Germany, her father, Gebhard Von Dießen I, was 55 and her mother, Richardis von Sponheim, was 59. She married Diepold II von Berg-Schelklingen about 1149. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died after 1150, in Berg, Ahrweiler, Rhineland-Palatinate, Germany."},"et":{"Abt 1125–nach 1150":"umbes 1125–pärast 1150","1097–1161":"1097–1161","1125–1150":"1125–1150","1097–1165":"1097–1165","1120–1165":"1120–1165","1071–1102":"1071–1102","1067–1151":"1067–1151","1165":"1165","1120":"1120","1097":"1097","Abt 1125":"umbes 1125","1151":"1151","1150":"1150","1161":"1161","1071":"1071","1125":"1125","1102":"1102","nach 1150":"pärast 1150","1067":"1067","um 1149":"umbes 1149","Berg, Ahrweiler, Rheinland-Pfalz, Deutschland":"Berg, Landkreis Ahrweiler, Rheinland-Pfalz, Saksamaa","German Empire":"Saksamaa","Schwarzenberg, Freudenstadt, Württemberg, Germany":"Schwarzenberg, Freudenstadt, Württemberg, Saksamaa"},"fi":{"Abt 1125–nach 1150":"noin 1125–1150 jälkeen","1097–1161":"1097–1161","1125–1150":"1125–1150","1097–1165":"1097–1165","1120–1165":"1120–1165","1071–1102":"1071–1102","1067–1151":"1067–1151","1165":"1165","1120":"1120","1097":"1097","Abt 1125":"noin 1125","1151":"1151","1150":"1150","1161":"1161","1071":"1071","1125":"1125","1102":"1102","nach 1150":"1150 jälkeen","1067":"1067","um 1149":"noin 1149","Berg, Ahrweiler, Rheinland-Pfalz, Deutschland":"Berg, Landkreis Ahrweiler, Rheinland-Pfalz, Sak